    "body": "Our definition of a test contract is pretty vague right now. I'd say you can filter out any contract that has a function that starts with `test`... and that's about all we can do right now 😅\r\n\r\nThe relevant snippet starts here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/ad253042bf842e4db90776c88a5a235ea4536545/cli/src/compile.rs#L113\r\n\r\n`compiled_contracts` is of the type `BTreeMap<Version, Vec<(String, Contract)>>` where `Version` is the compiler version, string is the contract name (I presume, it might be the file path?) and `Contract` is this struct here, which contains an ABI:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/gakonst/ethers-rs/blob/919a570237b0d92cfa34737d8803514caaa62612/ethers-solc/src/artifacts/contract.rs#L16",
